              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Beam energy at first Sb target is 45.5 or 39.2 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "High purity (99.999%) antimony targets were prepared by",
                " electric sputtering onto aluminum disks, 0.038 mm",
                " thick and 13 mm dia, with purity of 99%.",
                "The uniformity of the thickness of antimony layer was",
                " better than 4%.",
                "Target thickness measured by using thermal neutron",
                " activation analysis via 121Sb(n,g)122Sb reaction.",
                "Sb thicknesses of 40-150 microgram per target.",
                "Seven antimony targets and several energy-degrading Al",
                " foils were placed in a stack.  The stack was wrapped",
                " with a 0.025 mm aluminium foil and was irradiated in",
                " an aluminum target holder."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Stacks were irradiated for about 1 hour",
                " with 5 micro-A proton beam in Faraday Cup.",
                "Beam energy at each target calculated using range-",
                " energy table of Bichsel (1972).",
                "Normal high resolution gamma-spectrometry method was",
                " applied."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE-IN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Standard deviation of replicate",
                " measurements reflect cumulative uncertainties in",
                " determination of target thickness, proton beam",
                " current, detector efficiency, counting statistics,",
                " in values used for gamma-ray intensities and nuclide",
                " half-lives, as well as statistical uncertainty in",
                " gamma photopeak count rates.",
                "Points given without uncertainty are from single",
                " determination at that energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
